==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acetous
<hw>A*ce"tous</hw> <pr>(#; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acetum</ets> vinegar, fr. <ets>acere</ets> to be sour.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a sour taste; sour; acid.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An
<xex>acetous</xex> spirit.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Boyle.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧A liquid of an
<xex>acetous</xex> kind.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp. Lowth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Causing, or connected with, acetification; <as>as,
<ex>acetous</ex> fermentation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Acetous acid</b></col>, <cd>a name formerly given to
vinegar, which is a dilute solution of acetic acid.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>acetphenetidin</ent>⟦br⟧
